text: I LOVED the movie! Though it didn't stay true to the book it was still funny! I'm really glad they chose the high school happy ending theme. I'm a sucker for these kind of movies and the message despite of what people might say was there. And it was very true, personal and beatiful.    Everyone is a duff. And it doesn't mean you have to be ugly or fat. It just means that everyone has felt like a fatso, ugly, pizza face, slut, etc...but gess what? So has the rest of us. Just suck it up, stop judging the others to make yourself feel better and accept yourself. ^^   Now for those bitching about the movie...sigh. You're often have to attract a wider audience with a movie, which is why the studios end up changing the plot to suit a wider taste.   Besides the fact that they don't have enough time to put in all the details, they also try to please everyone, which means sacrificing plot integrity. With a movie, studios often decide that they don't have the time to make relationships confusing if that is not the very main focus, so they make the end-pairing as obvious as possible. In a movie, they also try to make the characters more likeable as well to attract moviegoers.   That is probably why the sex scenes right at the beginning was taken out; otherwise, some people might think Bianca was a b*tch to lead him on the way she did. [Not that Wesley WAS lead on ;) ]

text: Okay some of these comments were just four ways from stupid. What kind of person says they've "stopped reading books because Hollywood can't come up with original ideas"? Isn't that the EXACT reason why you SHOULD be reading books? Also I READ the book. I loved the book. Yes I was a little disappointed that the movie didn't follow the book. This doesn't make it a bad movie. It's s teen movie and not all teens have the maturity to understand the book and what it means.   I mean, damn! The fact that there are so many comments about the fact that Bianca isn't fat or ugly prove my point. In the books she's not described as far or ugly either. But the term DUFF is a generalisation which is actually explained in the freaking TRAILER even. So I get why the movie was dumbed down.   But the movie does try to give out the general moral of the book. The basic being that we all feel Inferior to our friends at one point or another and that we shouldn't allow that to stop us being ourselves.

text: Stop saying stuff like "people should not be upset bc it's not exactly like the book," fans of the book have every right to be upset about this movie being completely different than the book bc now no one will ever be able to get the movie rights to tell the REAL story of Bianca and Wesley. Now the real "duff"  storyline will never be seen in movie theaters bc some dumb Hollywood producers wanted to make money off of yet another dumb "no bullying" "chick flick." It's hilarious how Hollywood has no new and interesting stories coming out and when they finally decided to make a movie based off of an original and interesting storyline, they change it to be unoriginal and predictable. I understand that if they had stuck to the books original storyline that would have caused the movie to probably be less family family friendly and less pre-teen friendly, but come on Hollywood GROW SOME BALLS. Stop trying to make another Mean Girls. In fact Mean Girls and "easy A" were success BECAUSE they weren't afraid of being more honest and raunchy. This movie COULD have been the Mean Girls if it had just stuck to the original script and been it's own movie, rather then copy and pasting.
